		<contents_en>New Features:\nAdded support for using QQ Music as a download service, with corresponding options added in General Settings.\nImplemented changing playback speed without pitch shifting when using the BASS kernel; added pitch-shifting functionality to playback controls.\nAdded search list functionality to the Find dialog.\nAdded the "Remember last playback position" option in "Playback Settings," allowing playback to start from the beginning when switching lists.\nAdded Traditional Chinese language support.\nAdded an option in Options Settings → Media Library to merge different versions of the same song in the Now Playing list.\nAdded the "Remove top border of title bar" option in Options Settings → Appearance Settings to resolve the issue of a white border at the top of the window title bar.\nAdjusted the background color in Dark Mode when "Enable Background" is unchecked.\nThe minimum UI refresh interval has been adjusted to 2 milliseconds.\nAdded the "Command-line behavior for opening single audio files" option in Playback Settings.\nAdded an option in Options Settings → Playback Settings to disable screen sleep during full-screen playback (#868).\nAdded the folder browsing element medialibFolderExplore.\nAdded the search box element searchBox.\nAdded the interface switcher element elementSwitcher for switching stackElement.\nThe navigation bar element navigationBar now supports configuring navigation bar buttons through the child element navigationItem.\nThe "Groove Music Style (Style)" interface now supports entering the playback page by clicking on an album.\nResolved the issue where two identical button elements could not be added to the same interface.\nAdded display panel functionality, including a new playback queue panel and user-customizable panels.\nUpdated Interface 4 with a new left-side navigation bar.\n\nBug Fixes:\nFixed the issue where double-clicking in the mini-mode playlist did not play the track.\nFixed the issue where the "Update Source" option in General Settings was not saved to the configuration file.\nFixed the issue in the lyric edit dialog where executing "Replace Time Tag" or "Delete Time Tag" on a line without a time tag would delete the entire line.\nFixed the issue in the lyric edit dialog where executing "Swap Lyrics and Translation" without a translation would result in an extra " / ".\nFixed the issue in the Media Library dialog → Folders tab where the "Play Selected" button remained grayed out after selecting a folder.\nFixed the issue in Options Settings where album cover files and default background images using relative paths might not be recognized.\nFixed the flickering issue in the title bar area when activating the window after removing the top border.\nFixed lyric search failures caused by changes to the NetEase Cloud Music API.\nFixed the issue where some audio files would get stuck at the end of playback when using the FFMPEG kernel.\nFixed the issue in the format conversion dialog where the progress bar remained at 0% if conversion failed to start due to an error.\nFixed the issue in Options Settings → Appearance Settings where directly editing the "External Image File Name" text box and clicking OK would not save the changes.\nFixed the issue where album information was incorrectly passed as artist information to the system media transport controls.\nFixed the issue where, after maximizing the main window on a secondary monitor, minimizing and then clicking the taskbar button would cause the window to display on the primary monitor.\nFixed various crash issues.</contents_en>
